org.gridlab.gat
Class URI

java.lang.Object
  org.gridlab.gat.URI
All Implemented Interfaces:
Comparable, Serializable
public class URI
extends Object
implements Serializable, Comparable

This class implements URIs. It is API compatible with java.net.URI. However, the standard Java class has a bug. The Java URI class does not work correctly if you omit the hostname in a URI. For example:
file:// /
and
== not set (empty string)
and
== /bin/date
then the correct URI is
file:////bin/date
So four slashes in total after the "file:"
if the path would be a relative path such as foo/bar, the URI would be:
file:///foo/bar (three slashes because of the empty hostname).
However, the Java URI class getPath() method will return "/foo/bar" as the path instead of "foo/bar"...

Also note that relative URIs are relative to $home on the machine it refers to, NOT relative to the current working directory.

public boolean isCompatible(String scheme)
Checks whether this URI is "compatible" with the given scheme If this URI has the same scheme, it is compatible. When this URI has "any" as scheme, or no scheme at all, it is also compatible.

Parameters:

Returns:
true: the URIs are compatible
